Weather App Documentation

Overview
The "Weather App" allows users to retrieve and display weather information for a specific city. It utilizes the OpenWeatherMap API to fetch real-time weather data based on the user's input of the city name.

HTML Structure
Header: Displays the title of the application, "Weather App."
Input Section: Contains an input field for the user to enter the city name and a "Search" button to initiate the weather search.
Weather Information Section: Shows the retrieved weather information for the city entered by the user, including city name, weather icon, temperature, and weather description.

CSS Styling
Overall Styling: Provides a centered layout with a background gradient for visual appeal.
Input and Button Styling: Defines styles for the input field and search button to maintain consistency.
Weather Information Styling: Formats the weather details such as temperature, weather icon, and description for clear presentation.

JavaScript Functionality
Fetching Weather Data: Utilizes the OpenWeatherMap API to retrieve weather data based on the provided city name.
Displaying Weather Data: Renders the retrieved data, including city name, weather icon, temperature, and description, dynamically onto the webpage.

Usage
Search for Weather: Enter the name of a city in the input field and click the "Search" button to get the current weather information for that city.
View Weather Details: Once the search is successful, the city name, weather icon, temperature, and description will be displayed.

Notes
API Key: Replace '7d939c06ec5105a806c2ab1ca5838e9d' with your own OpenWeatherMap API key in the script.js file.
Error Handling: If the city name is not provided or if there's an error in fetching data, appropriate alerts will be shown to the user.

This documentation outlines the functionalities, structure, usage instructions, and notes for the "Weather App." It provides a straightforward interface for users to access current weather information for any desired city. Adjustments and enhancements can be made to tailor the application further, based on specific requirements or preferences.